1. What is JavaScript?
Interview Answer

JavaScript is a high-level, interpreted scripting language used to make web pages interactive and dynamic.

Without JavaScript:

HTML → Structure
CSS → Styling
JavaScript → Behaviour
Example

Imagine YouTube.

HTML creates

Video
Buttons
Comments

CSS makes them beautiful.

JavaScript makes

Play button work
Pause button work
Like button increase count
Comments appear instantly

Without JavaScript, websites would look like a newspaper.

With JavaScript, they become applications.

Easy Analogy

Think of a Car.

HTML = Car Body 🚗

CSS = Paint + Design 🎨

JavaScript = Engine 🔥

Interview One-Liner

JavaScript is used to add logic and interactivity to websites.

2. Data Types

JavaScript has 8 data types

Primitive (7)

These store a single value.

Data Type	Example
String	"Lucky"
Number	25
BigInt	123456789n
Boolean	true
Undefined	let x;
Null	null
Symbol	Symbol()
Non Primitive (1)

Object

Everything complex is an object.

Examples

let person={
 name:"Lucky",
 age:22
}

Array

let arr=[10,20,30]

Function

function hello(){}

Even Arrays and Functions are Objects internally.

Interview Trick
typeof null

Output

object

This is a famous JavaScript bug.

Interview Answer

Primitive types store a single value while non-primitive types store collections of values.

3. Hoisting

This is among the Top 5 JavaScript interview questions.

Simple Meaning

Before executing code,

JavaScript moves declarations to the top.

Not values.

Example

console.log(a);

var a=10;

Internally JavaScript sees

var a;

console.log(a);

a=10;

Output

undefined

Remember

Declaration

var a;

is hoisted.

Initialization

a=10;

is NOT hoisted.

Functions are also hoisted.

hello();

function hello(){
console.log("Hi");
}

Works perfectly.

Interview One-Liner

Hoisting means JavaScript moves declarations to the top of their scope before execution.

4. debugger

Very easy.

let a=10;

debugger;

a++;

Execution stops here.

You can inspect variables.

Think of it as putting a checkpoint.

Interview Answer

debugger pauses code execution so developers can inspect variables and debug the program.

